title: Strong and light winds in the dream of a single or married man and woman

preview.html: Strong winds and hurricanes, as well as tornadoes, have the same meaning and meaning in a dream, as they are an expression of rapid and sudden changes, some of which are praiseworthy if these winds do not leave damage, and some indicate a problem if the winds or the storm has negative effects, such as demolishing houses and falling trees. Winds Light in a dream expresses a happy event or something that benefits him, especially if the dreamer feels like a light breeze or a cool breeze caressing his cheeks, moving his clothes, or moving the curtains. The wind in a dream is a prominent element of the basic elements or forces of nature, as well as fire, water, and earth. Interpretation of the wind In the dream of an unmarried girl, strong or powerful winds in the dream of an unmarried girl express harsh transformations on the psychological level, while it is also a sign of tension if the unmarried woman sees these winds laden with dust or dust. As for the winds accompanied by rain, they are praiseworthy and express a happy event. Because rain is a symbol of prosperity and tranquility, as well as happiness and emotional stability. A light wind or a cool breeze in an unmarried girl’s dream expresses complete psychological comfort. Perhaps the dream indicates that you are receiving happy news that warms your chest. Light winds are also a sign of light and positive transformations, both practical and emotional. Interpretation of wind in a dream for a married woman and a pregnant woman. Strong winds translate the brokenness of the soul and perhaps its fluctuations. Most women who see strong winds, storms, or storms in their dreams actually live in a state of constant stress, either due to financial need or family disputes. Lack of security within the home causes a married woman to see these violent natural phenomena and storms. Winds and hurricanes are images and scenes hidden in the subconscious mind that express a deep fear of the present and the future. The wind in a married woman’s dream can be a positive message in the dream if it is accompanied by rain or snow and expresses material well-being and security. As for a pregnant woman’s dream, the wind accompanied by rain heralds the birth of a child. Easy and blessed. Interpretation of seeing wind in a man’s dream. Interpretation of wind in a man’s dream depends on his situation. Strong winds or storms portend a risky matter, such as a man making a wrong decision in his life. Strong winds that uproot trees, plants, and plants express social unrest or negative transformations in the future, and strong winds can indicate God’s fears, and he was afraid of something expected to happen in the future. If a person sees in a dream that the wind calmed down after leaving the disaster, then this is the interpretation. It is said that the dreamer will feel calm and stable in life after a series of shocks or conflicts, whether on pain
